---
// Challenge Section
---

<section class="py-20 bg-white">
  <div class="container-custom">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">
        You Became a Financial Advisor to Help People, Not to 'Sell' to Them
      </h2>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-12 text-center">
        We understand. Traditional sales approaches feel uncomfortable, even inappropriate, 
        when you're dealing with people's financial futures.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Traditional Way Feels Wrong</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>• Pushy scripts that don't sound like you</li>
            <li>• Pressure tactics that damage trust</li>
            <li>• Focus on closing rather than helping</li>
            <li>• Techniques that feel manipulative</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">But You Still Need to Grow</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>• Your expertise deserves more clients</li>
            <li>• Your practice needs new business</li>
            <li>• You want to help more people</li>
            <li>• Growth shouldn't mean compromise</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 p-8 rounded-2xl">
        <blockquote class="text-lg italic text-gray-700 mb-4">
          "I knew I could help these clients with their financial planning, but I couldn't bring myself 
          to use the pushy tactics I'd been taught. There had to be a better way..."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600">
          - Sarah M., IFA, Workshop Participant
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="text-center mt-12">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 font-medium">
          The good news? There <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">is</span> a better way.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>